data.body:
Refs: #29442

Have `"echo": false` in yout tasks.json, notice the tasks still gets outputed in the panel, so it is crpytic to me what does this attribute do in the end.
Here's my tasks.json if needed

```
{
    // See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=733558
    // for the documentation about the tasks.json format
    "version": "2.0.0",
    "tasks": [
        {
            "type": "gulp",
            "task": "build",
            "presentation": {
                "echo": false,
                "reveal": "always",
                "focus": false,
                "panel": "shared"
            },
            "problemMatcher": [
                "$gulp-tsc"
            ]
        }
    ]
}
```

Testing #29490

My extension runs following code when invoking a command

```
vscode.debug.createDebugSession(getLaunchConfig(filePath, outDir))
				.then(debugSession => {
					vscode.debug.onDidTerminateDebugSession(e => {
						if (e.type === debugSession.type) {
							e.customRequest('workbench.debug.panel.action.clearReplAction');
							// vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.debug.panel.action.clearReplAction');
						}
					})
				});
```

e.customRequest('workbench.debug.panel.action.clearReplAction') is not executing the command.
